        <xsd:documentation>
            <xhtml:h2 ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">Implementation Notes</xhtml:h2>
            <xhtml:p ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">A MAC.XML is used in conjuction with 
                TDF collections as structured assertions that indicate how objects in a trusted data 
                collection are related. A Trusted Data Collection conforms to the MAC specification when 
                it contains a structured assertion with scope TDC and a multiAudience element. The 
                multiAudienceObject element may also appear to provide additional information about each 
                object in the collection regarding it's relationship to the larger collection. In this way 
                MAC can be used to describe a set of tearlined assets, or other related data sets as needed. 
                Its structure is similar to:</xhtml:p>
            <xhtml:ul>
                    <xhtml:p ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">A 
                        <xhtml:a href="IC-TDF_xsd_Element_TrustedDataCollection.html#TrustedDataCollection">
                            tdf:TrustedDataCollection</xhtml:a>
                    </xhtml:p>
                    <xhtml:ul>
                        <xhtml:li ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">has an assertion
                            <xhtml:a href="MAC-XML_xsd_Element_mac_MultiAudience.html#MultiAudience">
                                mac:MultiAudience</xhtml:a>
                        </xhtml:li>
                        <xhtml:li ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">optionally has an assertion
                            <xhtml:a href="MAC-XML_xsd_Element_mac_MultiAudienceObject.html#MultiAudienceObject">
                                mac:MultiAudienceObject</xhtml:a>
                        </xhtml:li>
                    </xhtml:ul>
            </xhtml:ul>
        </xsd:documentation>
